            <div class="step-by-step-guide">
                <!-- Phase 1 -->
                <section id="phase1" class="build-phase">
                    <h3>Phase 1: Foundation & First Floor Layout</h3>
                    <p>We'll start by laying out the base of the pagoda and building up the first main floor.</p>

                    <div class="build-step">
                        <h4>Step 1.1: Outline the Base</h4>
                        <p>Using Stone Bricks, create a 21x21 block square outline on flat ground. This will be the outermost edge of your foundation.</p>
                        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x350.png?text=Step+1.1+Image" alt="Step 1.1: Base Outline">
                    </div>

                    <div class="build-step">
                        <h4>Step 1.2: Raise Foundation Platform</h4>
                        <p>Fill the outlined area with Cobblestone, raising it 1 block high. Then add another layer of Stone Bricks on top of the Cobblestone.</p>
                        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x350.png?text=Step+1.2+Image" alt="Step 1.2: Raised Platform">
                    </div>

                    <div class="build-step">
                        <h4>Step 1.3: Place Corner Pillars</h4>
                        <p>At each corner of the Stone Brick platform, place Dark Oak Wood Logs 5 blocks high.</p>
                        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x350.png?text=Step+1.3+Image" alt="Step 1.3: Corner Pillars">
                        <p class="tip"><strong>Tip:</strong> Ensure your ground is level before starting for best results.</p>
                    </div>
                    <!-- ... More steps for Phase 1 ... -->
                </section>

                <!-- Phase 2 -->
                <section id="phase2" class="build-phase">
                    <h3>Phase 2: Second Floor & Lower Roof</h3>
                    <p>Now we'll construct the second story and the iconic sloped roof for the first tier.</p>

                    <div class="build-step">
                        <h4>Step 2.1: First Floor Walls</h4>
                        <p>Connect the Dark Oak pillars with Spruce Wood Planks to form the walls of the first floor. Leave openings for doors and windows as desired.</p>
                        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x350.png?text=Step+2.1+Image" alt="Step 2.1: First Floor Walls">
                    </div>
                    <div class="build-step">
                        <h4>Step 2.2: Lower Roof Eaves</h4>
                        <p>Using Dark Oak Stairs and Slabs, begin creating the overhanging eaves of the first roof tier. This typically extends 2-3 blocks out from the walls.</p>
                        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x350.png?text=Step+2.2+Image" alt="Step 2.2: Lower Roof Eaves">
                    </div>
